kfreebsd-config (0.0.4) unreleased; urgency=low

  * Remove nfsclient (doesn't autoload as module) and ums (will stay in kernel
    image) from "other" list.
  * config:  Lower priority of network template (to "medium").
  * Don't mess with network interfaces when they aren't being used.
    - control (Depends): Nuke netbase.
    - postinst: Only invoke /etc/init.d/networking when it exists.
  * Rise Priority to "required".
  * templates:  Remove obsolete drivers snd_sb8 and snd_sb16.  Improve
    description of snd_sbc which superceeds them.
  * Add snd_probe command to detect soundcard, and refer to it in sound
    template.
  * Never mess with acpi module in postinst.

 -- Robert Millan <rmh@aybabtu.com>  Tue,  2 Aug 2005 13:48:10 +0200

kfreebsd-config (0.0.3) unreleased; urgency=low

  * postinst: Actualy, unload modules when they have been removed, not when they
    have *not* been.
  * Invoke /etc/init.d/networking to make sure that messing with network modules
    doesn't kill the interface.
    - postinst
    - control: Depend on netbase.
    - templates (network): Add warning about broken /etc/init.d/networking
    files (dhclient).

 -- Robert Millan <rmh@aybabtu.com>  Mon,  1 Aug 2005 15:48:26 +0200

